# gen45: the benchmark bridge. The SuperGLUE driver wraps each example as one
# line "...Passage: <P> Question: <Q> Answer yes or no." parrot0 matched none of
# it and abstained -> 0%, worse than a coin flip (it never guesses). This bridge
# recognizes the envelope, READS the passage through the existing extractor, and
# ANSWERS the question through the existing query modules -- emitting yes/no only
# when the answer is genuinely derivable. It is I/O wiring, not new reasoning and
# not a phrasebook: on open prose it still abstains, so the score measures real
# reasoning coverage. (On real validation that coverage is ~0 until the prose
# grammar grows -- the honest wall, D-2026-06-15e.)
# In-grammar passage -> the query is provable -> "yes".
> SuperGLUE BoolQ. Passage: barq is a soft drink. barq is a beverage. Question: is barq a beverage? Answer yes or no.
< yes
# Known-but-false predicate -> closed-world "no".
> SuperGLUE BoolQ. Passage: rex is a dog. rex is not a cat. Question: is rex a cat? Answer yes or no.
< no
# Open prose that does not parse -> honest abstention, never a guess.
> SuperGLUE BoolQ. Passage: the weather was lovely and everyone felt calm. Question: was the mood tense? Answer yes or no.
< I don't understand that yet.
